Sentencas: Possessing a high oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) activity is one of the most important prerequisites for the cathode to ensure an efficient solid oxide fuel cell.
Titulo: Enhancing oxygen reduction reaction activity of perovskite oxides cathode for solid oxide fuel cells using a novel anion doping strategy

Sentencas: Herein, a highly active cathode is developed by doping the fluorine anion in anion sites of perovskite oxides (ABO(3)).
Titulo: Enhancing oxygen reduction reaction activity of perovskite oxides cathode for solid oxide fuel cells using a novel anion doping strategy

Sentencas: The electrocatalytic activities of three different cathode samples including the original perovskite La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta (LSCF), the doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O2.95-delta F0.05 (LSCFF0.05) and La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O2.9-delta F0.1 (LSCFF0.1) are comparatively investigated.
Titulo: Enhancing oxygen reduction reaction activity of perovskite oxides cathode for solid oxide fuel cells using a novel anion doping strategy

Sentencas: The fluorine doped perovskites reveal higher electrochemical performance than the original perovskite.
Titulo: Enhancing oxygen reduction reaction activity of perovskite oxides cathode for solid oxide fuel cells using a novel anion doping strategy

Sentencas: Based on three cathodes of LSCF, LSCFF0.05 and LSCFF0.1 operated at 850 degrees C, the measured area specific resistance was 0.018, 0.017 and 0.91 Omega cm(2), respectively; and the respective maximum power density of the single fuel cell using the 9-mu m-thick YSZ electrolyte was 754, 1005, and 737 mW cm(-2).
Titulo: Enhancing oxygen reduction reaction activity of perovskite oxides cathode for solid oxide fuel cells using a novel anion doping strategy

Sentencas: Such performance results vividly indicate that, the obtained perovskite oxyfluoride by doping an optimum amount of F ions can efficiently improve ORR activity and thus is a feasible strategy to develop cathode for highperformance solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Enhancing oxygen reduction reaction activity of perovskite oxides cathode for solid oxide fuel cells using a novel anion doping strategy
